2. Gas Fee: The PoSA block validation algorithm achieves consensus at a much lower fee than PoW. Also, gas fees on #Ethereum increase with demand and traffic, while the #BNBChain has good stability. In other words, BEP-20 tokens are cheaper to transact in than ERC-20 ones. (9/11)

1. Block Verification Speed: #Ethereum uses a Proof of Work (PoW) consensus algorithm, while #BNBChain uses Proof of Staked Authority (PoSA). POW's block time is about 15 seconds, whereas BNB Chain's is 3 seconds. Thus, BEP-20 token transactions are faster than ERC-20's. (8/11)

ERC-20 and BEP-20 standards are owned by the Ethereum Foundation and Binance Organisation respectively. The standards define the coding parameters that must be adhered to for tokens to be created and deployed on #Ethereum and #BNBChain networks. (3/11)
